The paper discusses the use of citation data in predicting university rankings, which falls under the domain of digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The analysis also involves the use of machine learning techniques, which could be categorized under cybernetics (cs.CY) and signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the study involves evaluating the performance of research evaluation exercises, which could be classified under cryptography and security (cs.CR).
